ull, "display_name": "PaperLander Demo", "keywords": ["paper", "rocket", "gravity", "cute", "free"], "long_description": "PaperLander is a fragile rocket made out of - you guessed it - paper. He lives in PaperGalaxy, a low gravitational fantasy world far far away, made mostly out of paper too.\n\nBut now the Galaxy is in danger. A Space Storm is approaching and threatens to tear it apart. Only one thing can stop the Storm: The Great Anti-Storm Ion Cannon! But it works only with Proto-Stars. And Proto-Stars are scattered in the Galaxy, across its many Sectors. These Sectors are connected by a network of teleporters that activate upon landing. PaperLander's mission is to find and collect those Stars, pass through the Sectors using the teleporters and bring them to the Anti-Storm Ion Cannon in time to save the Galaxy!\n\nBuild your own PaperLander here: http://thiswayupgames.com/PaperLanderModel.pdf\n\n--------------------------------\nPlease note that this demo is not compatible with Oculus Go", "short_description": "PaperLander is a fragile rocket made out of - you guessed it - paper. He lives in PaperGalaxy, a low gravitational fantasy world far far away, made mostly out of paper too.\n\nBuild your own PaperLander here: http://thiswayupgames.com/PaperLanderModel.pdf\n\nBut now the Galaxy is in danger. A Space Storm is approaching and threatens to tear it apart. Only one thing can stop the Storm: The Great Anti-Storm Ion Cannon! But it works only with Proto-Stars, which are scattered in the Galaxy."}]}, "developer_name": null, "developer_privacy_policy_url": "http://thiswayupgames.com/privacy.html", "developer_terms_of_service_url": "http://thiswayupgames.com/terms.html", "publisher_name": "Self Published", "support_website_url": null, "website_url": "http://thiswayupgames.com/", "category": "GAMES", "comfort_rating": "COMFORTABLE_FOR_MOST", "comfort_tags": [], "context_category": null, "context_topics": [], "external_subscription_type": "NOT_REQUIRED", "genres": ["A